@node SPINE "Spined Wurm"

@{b}Spined Wurm@{ub}

Color   = Green
Rarity  = SH(C)
Type    = Summon Wurm (5/4)
Cost    = 4G
Artist  = Keith Parkinson


Flavor Text: @{i}"As it moved, the wurm's spines gathered up bits of
              flowstone, which took the shapes of dead villager's heads.
              Each head spoke a single sound, but if taken together,
              they said, 'Alas for the living.'" -Dal myth of the wurm@{ub}

 @{b}NO RULINGS@{ub}

@endnode
@node TEMPT "Tempting Licid"

@{b}Tempting Licid@{ub}

Color   = Green
Rarity  = SH(U)
Type    = Summon Licid (2/2)
Cost    = 2G
Artist  = Randy Gallegos

Text(SH): <GT>: Tempting Licid loses this ability and becomes a creature
          enchantment that reads "All creatures able to block enchanted
          creature do so" instead of a creature. Move Tempting Licid onto
          target creature. You may pay G to end this effect.


 @{b}NO RULINGS@{ub}

@endnode
@node VERDA "Verdant Touch"

@{b}Verdant Touch@{ub}

Color   = Green
Rarity  = SH(R)
Type    = Sorcery
Cost    = 1G
Artist  = DiTerlizzi

Text(SH): Buyback 3 (You may pay an additional 3 when you play this spell.
          If you do, put it into your hand instead of your graveyard as
          part of the spell's effect.)
          Target land becomes a 2/2 creature permanently. (This creature
          still counts as a land.)


 @{b}NO RULINGS@{ub}

@endnode
@node VOLRA "Volrath's Gardens"

@{b}Volrath's Gardens@{ub}

Color   = Green
Rarity  = SH(R)
Type    = Enchantment
Cost    = 1G
Artist  = Rob Alexander

Text(SH): <2>, Tap a creature you control: Gain 2 life. Play this ability
          as a sorcery.

Flavor Text: @{i}"Watch yourself," warned Starke. "These plants aren't nice
              when they're hungry."@{ub}

 @{b}NO RULINGS@{ub}

@endnode
@node WALLO "Wall of Blossoms"

@{b}Wall of Blossoms@{ub}

Color   = Green
Rarity  = SH(U)
Type    = Summon Wall (0/4)
Cost    = 1G
Artist  = Heather Hudson

Text(SH): (Walls cannot attack.)
          When Wall of Blossoms comes into play, draw a card.

Flavor Text: @{i}Each flower identical, every leaf and
              petal disturbingly exact.@{ub}

 @{b}NO RULINGS@{ub}

